\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 30. J. planifolius} R. Br.,{\i  Prodr. Fl. Nov. Holl.} 259 (1810). Caespitose perennial, often flowering in the first year. Stems 10-30(-60) cm, with usually c. 10 basal leaves. Leaves much shorter than the stem, 2-5(-10) mm wide, flat or slightly involute; auricles absent. Inflorescence of (1-)4-12(-50) dense, globular heads, each head usually 8- to 10-flowered. Perianth-segments 1·5-3 mm, subequal, ovate to lanceolate, dark brown, the outer acuminate, the inner obtuse. Stamens 3, almost as long as the perianth; anthers 1/3 as long as the filaments. Capsule exceeding the perianth, trigonous-obovoid, with a mucro c. 0·5 mm, dark brown. Seeds 0·35-0·4 mm, broadly ellipsoid, without appendages. {\i Bogs and lake-margins. Naturalized in W. Ireland.} [Hb.] ({\i Temperate South America, New Zealand, Australia}.)
\par

