\pard\f0\fs28  Subgen. {\b Juncinella} V. Krecz. & Gontsch. Small annuals, caespitose or with a single stem. Leaves and bracts not pungent. All leaves basal on flowering stems. Sheaths large, leaf-like, the lamina small, flat to subterete, without sclerenchyma-strands in the margin. Flowers solitary on the stem or in clusters; involucral bracteoles absent. Seeds prominently reticulate.
\par

